# UI buttons and crawl actions

Canonical skill: [`ai/skills/react-inertia-frontend/SKILL.md`](../../ai/skills/react-inertia-frontend/SKILL.md)

## Buttons

- Prefer `@jooservices/react-action-buttons` via thin wrappers [`Button`](resources/js/Components/ui/Button.tsx) / [`ActionBar`](resources/js/Components/ui/ActionBar.tsx).
- Do **not** add raw `rounded-md bg-*` button classes in pages or feature components.
- Legacy XFlickr variant names map onto JOO classes in [`buttonVariants.ts`](resources/js/lib/buttonVariants.ts):
  - `primary` → JOO `primary`
  - `primaryDark` → JOO `dark`
  - `secondary` → JOO `secondary`
  - `connect` → JOO `info`
  - `destructive` → JOO `danger`
  - `warning` → JOO `warning`
  - `ghost` / `link` → JOO `ghost`

## Crawl actions

- Use [`CrawlActionBar`](resources/js/Components/Flickr/CrawlActionBar.tsx) everywhere crawl, download, or upload is triggered.
- Do **not** import crawl dropdown internals from pages — they belong inside `CrawlActionBar`.
- Scopes: `account` (Flickr accounts table) or `contact` (contacts list rows, contact detail).

## Cards

- Use [`Card`](resources/js/Components/ui/Card.tsx) (`BaseCard`) / [`MetricCard`](resources/js/Components/ui/MetricCard.tsx) (`StatCard`) for panels and stats.
- Flickr/Storage settings use [`ProviderCard`](resources/js/Components/ui/ProviderCard.tsx) — domain-only (not in JOO packages).
